snippet.textDisplay:
You need to smoke that mr2, aircooled engines rulez! #aircooledmafia

By the way, this venturis are too big. I usually use 26 here in my shop. And to make serious power, put some e85 in it. Aren't that complicated, adjust the carbs, take the heads out and shrink the combustion chamber (something around 13x1 compression ratio) and you will need a distributor to work well on e85, here in Brazil we have that OEM from VW.

DM me if you guys need some info. On my racing engines 1584cc (1.6L) i made 130hp at the wheels!
